OL,3,CEx-miners extend strike at the
OL,4,Cnational pit museum
OL,6,F"They're desperate to be back doing
OL,7,Fwhat they love. But they want to be
OL,8,Fpaid fairly, and treated with respect.
OL,10,F"If the chief executive continues to
OL,11,Frefuse to negotiate, staff have no
OL,12,Fchoice but to continue their strike."
OL,14,FPhilip Marshall, Chair of the Board of
OL,15,FTrustees said: "We are disappointed by
OL,16,FUNISON's decision to extend the period
OL,17,Fof industrial action to Sunday 12
OL,18,FOctober, but we fully respect the
OL,19,Fright of employees to carry out
OL,20,Findustrial action if done in a
OL,21,Fpeaceful and lawful manner.
